Flev <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uabadacus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abadacus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/25/02 2:53:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=280.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Your best bet...</span><hr size=1> I have tried the idea out before and it does work, but you have to think &quot;Outside the Box&quot;, so to speak.<br>
<br>
What I mean by that is to use the world geometry to your favor.  A couple of things first....<br>
<br>
The only worthwhile spells to use would be Winds of Gelid and SuperNova, as they do indeed have the extra radius.  Jyll's won't work well enough for it to be effective in this case.<br>
<br>
Wyverns are actually a good mob to try them on because you have plenty of them, assuming they are not camped, are light blue to a 60, and you have plenty of room to negotiate a pull.  But most importantly, you have a cliff, that you can climb easily enough using Levitation.<br>
<br>
The idea is this:  Pull and bunch up the Wyverns on the beach, but giving yourself enough time to climb the cliff before they have a chance to reach it.  You must be stopped at the cliff edge or slightly beyong it before the Wyverns reach the bottom portion of the cliff.  Put yourself in 3rd person view, so that you can see the cliff face, and the mobs following you.  What this does is simple, it gives you time to cast your spell when you know they are approaching your range, but still have the physical distance to travel to reach you (straight up the cliff).  You must be far enough from the cliff face to prevent melee damage, and close enough for the spell to take effect (6 seconds for both Super Nova and Winds of Gelid).  <br>
<br>
Regardless of whether it works or not, you will have to reposition the mobs for every cast of SN and WoG, as there is a significant recast delay, and one nuke will not take them out.  Also, Winds of Gelid is cold based, so may present a problem with Wyverns.  I don't hunt them, but seems to me that they may be cold resistant.  That and both spells are very high in mana cost.<br>
<br>
I have not tried farting around with the Wyverns yet, though likely to do so just to test out my tactic in the near future.  See if this works for you.  You will need good timing, a good connection, and most importantly, Gnomish balls of Steel to pull it off.<br>
<br>
Abadacus RuneMaster<br>
Gnomish Sorceror<br>
